'with sharing' enforces the running user's record-level sharing rules (org-wide defaults, role hierarchy, sharing rules) for all SOQL queries and DML in that class. 'without sharing' runs in system context, ignoring sharing rules. A class declared with neither keyword inherits the sharing setting of the class that called it (or runs without sharing if there is no calling context).

Example - a controller that should only show Accounts the current user can see should be 'with sharing':

public with sharing class AccountListController {
    public List<Account> getVisibleAccounts() {
        return [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account];
    }
}

A scheduled job that must clean up records regardless of the running user's access would typically be 'without sharing':

public without sharing class NightlyDataCleanupJob {
    public void purgeStaleRecords() {
        delete [SELECT Id FROM Stale_Record__c WHERE CreatedDate < :Date.today().addDays(-365)];
    }
}

